  "texts": [
    "○ Q, K, and V are matrices of queries, keys, and values for all tokens.",
    "○ K t is the transpose of K. ○ The multiplication Q × K t computes the attention scores for all pairs of tokens simultaneously.",
    "This mechanism allows the model to focus on relevant parts of the input while generating output.",
    "For example, in the sentence \"The cat sat on the mat because it was soft, \" the model can accurately capture that \"it\" refers to \"the mat\" by assigning higher attention weights between these tokens.",
    "One challenge in processing sequences simultaneously is maintaining the sense of order in the data, as transformers do not process inputs sequentially like RNNs."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}